    <article class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-5 <%= 'lg:col-span-2' unless @project.managed_by?(current_user) %>">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Ingest endpoint</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">
        POST to
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">/api/v1/ingest_events</code>
        with header
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code>.
        Accepted requests are limited to 1,200 per minute per token by default; <code>429</code> responses include retry headers.
      </p>
      <% if @project.integration_android? || @project.integration_ios? %>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">
          Mobile apps should ask your backend for short-lived ingest tokens from
          <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">POST /api/v1/mobile_ingest_tokens</code>.
          Do not ship the project API key in an APK or IPA.
        </p>
      <% end %>
      <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">
        First event path for
        <strong class="text-slate-900"><%= @project.integration_label %></strong>.
        <% if @project.integration_cfml? %>
          Send one controlled exception from Lucee or ColdFusion with <code>cfhttp</code>.
        <% elsif @project.integration_python? %>
          Install <code>logister-python</code>, then send one web or worker exception.
        <% elsif @project.integration_dotnet? %>
          Use <code>Logister.AspNetCore</code> for one request exception, or the base client from a worker.
        <% elsif @project.integration_javascript? %>
          Install <code>logister-js</code>, then send one Node, Express, or worker exception.
        <% elsif @project.integration_cloudflare_pages? %>
          Manual telemetry is the working path today; send one metric or deployment record.
        <% elsif @project.integration_android? %>
          Install <code>org.logister:logister-android</code> and send one event through a backend-issued token.
        <% elsif @project.integration_ios? %>
          Add <code>logister-ios</code> and send one event through a backend-issued token.
        <% elsif @project.integration_http_api? %>
          POST one JSON event from your runtime, script, worker, or custom client.
        <% else %>
          Install <code>logister-ruby</code> and send one known Rails or Ruby exception.
        <% end %>
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">
        For waterfall charts, send <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">span</code>
        payloads with <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">trace_id</code>,
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">span_id</code>, and
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">duration_ms</code>.
      </p>
      <pre class="<%= project_setup_code_block_class %>"><code>{
  "event": {
    "event_type": "error",
    "level": "error",
    "message": "NoMethodError in CheckoutService",
    "fingerprint": "checkout-nomethoderror",
    "occurred_at": "2026-02-14T12:00:00Z",
    "context": { "environment": "production" }
  }
}</code></pre>
    </article>
